node.text:
Some need drugs to get high.  I simply need to listen to music.

It taps into every aspect of my soul.

The math side
The reflection side
The imagination side

Songs take me to many places.  It helps me travel.

Listening to Bronski beat “small town boy” takes me back to Germany at the refugee camp.

Listening to Foreigner “I want to know what love is” takes me back to the Army at Fort Campbell, Kentucky.

Listening to Sting “Fields of Gold” takes me back to Grad Night at magic mountain waiting in line for log jammer.

Listening to Jacques Brel “ne me quitte pas” takes me back to driving towards bandar Pahlavi in Iran with my family.

Listening to Kenny Rogers “Lady” takes me back to my wedding.

Listening to Celly Cel “It’s going down tonight” takes me back to Palm Springs with my friends.

Listening to David Guetta “The world is mine” takes me back to running my sales office in Granada Hills & Northridge.

Music soothes my soul.

I thank God for the ability to listen to great music.

I feel like I’m the luckiest man alive... even on days when nothing goes right!

Love ya!

node.text:
Basic formula to stay United.

1.  We will NEVER agree on everything and that’s ok.

2. No one has the answer to everything.

3. Great ideas are a byproduct of opposing ideas clashing. Censorship divides.

4. It’s easier to avoid tough conversations instead of facing them.

But freedom is worth it.

#reunitedstates

node.text:
Don’t buy the BS.

Every day I run into amazing people.

Every day people validate why the future looks bright.

Every day I see examples of great men and women.

Every day I see strangers who who help other strangers without caring about the politics, color of their skin or religion.

It makes no difference to me whether you’re white, black, latino, asian, educated, not educated, tall, short, married, single, republican, democrat, independent or someone who could care less for politics.

But if you’re a bully, a manipulator, a divider, a person who plays games who gets joy from destroying a beautiful family, a great company or country, you won’t win in the end.

History doesn’t them.

Future looks bright!
